# Voucher Approval Status Rules

## Sequential Approval Flow (3-step)

Steps in order: `accountant (1/3) ‚Üí legalRep (2/3) ‚Üí treasurer (3/3)`

Configured in `Master Company` sheet Column I (approver emails, comma-separated in role order). Always read approver emails from `Master Company` ‚Äî never hardcode them.

## `getVoucherSummary` ‚Äî Progress Calculation (`handleGetVoucherSummary`)

The summary endpoint serves the dashboard card list. It must correctly compute `approvalProgress` for each voucher without reading the large MetaJSON column (Column R).

### Primary: status column "(N/3)" pattern
Parse the `(N/3)` substring from Column J (status). This is authoritative and always takes precedence.

```js
function progressFromStatus(status) {
  const m = (status || '').toString().match(/\((\d)\/3\)/);
  if (m) return parseInt(m[1]);
  if (status === 'Approved' || status === 'ƒê√£ duy·ªát' || status === 'Fully Approved' || status === 'Received') return 3;
  return 0;
}
```

### Fallback: unique approver email Set (old data only)
For rows without `(N/3)` in status (pre-format data), count **unique approver emails** from Column P across all rows of the same voucher. Use a `Set` ‚Äî never a plain counter.

**Critical:** Duplicate approval rows from the same person must count as 1, not N.
- `nhanh.nguyen@tl-c.com.vn` √ó 3 rows ‚Üí Set size = **1** ‚Üí 1/3 ‚úì
- `nhanh@x.com` + `le@x.com` + `linh@x.com` ‚Üí Set size = **3** ‚Üí 3/3 ‚úì

```js
// Map<voucherNumber, Set<approverEmail|approverName>>
const approvalEmailSetMap = new Map();

if (isApprovalAction(row[11])) {
  const approverEmail = (row[15] || '').toString().trim().toLowerCase();
  const approverKey = approverEmail
    || row[11].toString().replace(/^Duy·ªát b·ªüi\s*/i, '').trim()
    || ('_row_' + vNum);
  if (!approvalEmailSetMap.has(vNum)) approvalEmailSetMap.set(vNum, new Set());
  approvalEmailSetMap.get(vNum).add(approverKey);
}
```

### Combining primary + fallback
Always prefer `statusProgress` when non-zero. The fallback (`actionProgress`) is only used when the status column carries no progress info at all:

```js
const statusProgress = progressMap.get(vNum) || 0;
const actionProgress = Math.min((approvalEmailSetMap.get(vNum) || new Set()).size, 3);
const bestProgress = statusProgress > 0 ? statusProgress : actionProgress;
```

**Never use `Math.max(statusProgress, actionProgress)`** ‚Äî this lets duplicate rows override a correct status-based value.

## `getVoucherFromHistory` / `_getVoucherFromData_` ‚Äî Approval Reconstruction

Both functions scan `Voucher_History` rows and reconstruct the current approval state. Two independent checks run per row ‚Äî do NOT use `else if` between them:

```js
// 1. Email match: advance role if this approver's email matches a configured role
if (rowApproverEmail) {
  // match against companyApprovers[role].email for each role
}

// 2. Meta check: read stored companyApprovers from metaJson for this row
if (rowMeta && rowMeta.companyApprovers) {
  // apply stored approval state from this row's metaJson
}
```

**Why both must run:** If the configured email later changes (e.g. `nguyennhanh863@gmail.com` ‚Üí `nhanh.nguyen@tl-c.com.vn`), the email branch may not match old rows, but the meta branch can still reconstruct from the stored `companyApprovers`. Using `else if` would silently skip the meta branch whenever `rowApproverEmail` is truthy.

## Approver Email Consistency

- Approver emails in `Master Company` Column I **must exactly match** the `approvedBy` field written into `Voucher_History` MetaJSON Column R at approval time.
- Mismatched emails (e.g. personal Gmail vs workspace email) cause approval reconstruction to fail and allow duplicate approvals for the same step.
- Always verify: `Master Company` email = the email the approver is **logged in with** when approving.

## Frontend Display (`normalizeVoucherState` / `deriveVoucherStatusBadge`)

The frontend reads `voucher.meta.companyApprovers.approvalProgress` from the `getVoucherSummary` response:

```js
const progressRaw = voucher?.meta?.companyApprovers?.approvalProgress || '0/3';
const progressNum = parseInt(progressRaw.split('/')[0], 10) || 0;
// progressNum >= 3  ‚Üí  "ƒê√£ Duy·ªát (3/3)"  (approved bucket)
// progressNum 1-2   ‚Üí  "ƒêang Duy·ªát (N/3)" (in-progress bucket)
// progressNum === 0 ‚Üí  "Ch·ªù Duy·ªát (0/3)"  (pending bucket)
```

The `approvalProgress` field set by `getVoucherSummary` (via `bestProgress + '/3'`) is the single source of truth for dashboard badge display. If the backend sets it correctly, the frontend will display correctly without any separate `getApprovalStatus` call.

## Duplicate Approval Prevention (Backend Guards)

`_approveVoucherCoreWithSheet_` has two hard guards that run on every approval attempt:

```js
// Guard 1 ‚Äî same person trying to approve twice
if (companyApprovers.approvers[approverRole].status === 'approved') {
  return createResponse(false, 'B·∫°n ƒë√£ ph√™ duy·ªát phi·∫øu n√Ýy r·ªìi.');
}

// Guard 2 ‚Äî wrong person (out of sequence)
if (approverRole !== currentApprover) {
  return createResponse(false, 'Ch∆∞a ƒë·∫øn l∆∞·ª£t ph√™ duy·ªát. ƒêang ch·ªù: ' + currentApproverName);
}
```

These guards fire **before** any row is written to the sheet. Both `handleApproveVoucher` (single) and `handleBulkApprove` (batch) route through the same core, so both are protected.

**The guards only work correctly when reconstruction is correct.** If the email in `Master Company` mismatches the `approvedBy` field in history, reconstruction shows the role as "pending" ‚Üí Guard 1 passes ‚Üí duplicate row is written. Fix: keep emails consistent (see Approver Email Consistency above).

## Cleaning Up Duplicate Rows (`cleanupDuplicateApprovalRows`)

A one-time utility function in `VOUCHER_WORKFLOW_BACKEND.gs`. Run it directly from the Apps Script editor (no deployment needed):

1. Open Apps Script editor ‚Üí select `cleanupDuplicateApprovalRows` in the function dropdown
2. Set `DRY_RUN = true` ‚Üí **‚ñ∂ Run** ‚Üí check Execution Log to preview which rows will be deleted
3. Set `DRY_RUN = false` ‚Üí **‚ñ∂ Run** ‚Üí rows are deleted bottom-to-top (safe index handling)

**Logic:** Groups rows by `(voucherNumber + approverEmail)`. For each group with >1 entry, keeps the row with the latest timestamp and deletes the rest. Vouchers with legitimate multi-approver rows (different emails per step) are not touched.

## Protection Layers Summary

| Layer | What it does |
|---|---|
| `Master Company` Col I email | Must match the login email used at approval time |
| `else if` ‚Üí `if` in reconstruction | Meta check always runs, even when email is present but mismatched |
| Guard 1: "already approved" | Blocks re-approval by same person for same role |
| Guard 2: "not your turn" | Blocks out-of-sequence approval |
| `approvalEmailSetMap` Set fallback | Dashboard counts unique approver emails, not raw row count |
| `statusProgress > 0 ? sp : ap` | Status column value always wins over action-row count |
| `cleanupDuplicateApprovalRows` | One-time cleanup if duplicates were written before fixes deployed |

## Common Bugs to Avoid

| Bug | Symptom | Fix |
|-----|---------|-----|
| `Math.max(statusProgress, actionProgress)` with a plain counter | 3 duplicate rows = "ƒê√£ duy·ªát (3/3)" on dashboard | Use `Set` for action fallback; use `statusProgress > 0 ? sp : ap` |
| `else if (rowMeta && rowMeta.companyApprovers)` after email check | Reconstruction skips meta when email is present but doesn't match | Change to independent `if` blocks |
| Approver email mismatch between `Master Company` and history | Duplicate approvals for same step; `getApprovalStatus` returns wrong count | Align emails in `Master Company` Col I with login email |
| `setSharing` failure stopping file URL return | File uploads but shows "L·ªói upload" instead of link | Wrap `setSharing` in non-fatal try/catch |
